COUCH TALK IS LOOKING FOR YOU
✨ ROLE: TREY (Male, 26–29)

Trey is feminine energy in motion.

He’s beautiful.

He’s soft, bold, confident, and magnetic.

Lip gloss popping. Walk got rhythm. Voice got flavor.

He owns every room without trying.

Trey is:

 • Flamboyant but grounded

 • Feminine but strong

 • Emotional, expressive, honest

 • The friend who tells the truth with style

 • The one you can’t stop watching

He moves with grace.

He speaks with intention.

He carries beauty like power.

This role is for someone who is:

 • Comfortable in their femininity

 • Confident in their skin

 • Expressive in face, body, voice, and soul

 • Not afraid to shine

Trey isn’t a joke.

He isn’t a stereotype.

He is beauty with depth.

He is softness with strength.

He is feminine energy done right.

🎬 Film: Couch Talk

📍 Detroit-based production

💰 Paid role

items.text:
Looking for a female actor aged 18–40 for a short comedy film with dry British, cringe-style humour.

Filming will take place in Swansea on Saturday 7th February.

This is an independent project. I’m fresh out of uni and working on building my portfolio and confidence as a filmmaker.

Details:
 • Paid hourly
 • Transport and accommodation can be covered
 • Comedy is subtle, awkward, and character-based
 • Experience welcome but not required

Ideal for someone who enjoys deadpan delivery, uncomfortable silences, and understated British humour.

If interested, please message me with:
 • A short intro
 • Any acting experience or CV (if you have one)
 • A headshot or recent photo
 • Showreel (optional)

Happy to answer any questions. Thanks!

Happy New Year Fellow Actors!
We are thrilled to announce our next online casting workshop with the fabulous Leila Ali! 

The workshop will take place:

Saturday February 21st - 10am GMT - Zoom

Leila is a Casting Associate for Sonia Allam CDG. 

During her time with Sonia, Leila has worked on various television productions such as 'Better' (BBC), 'Passenger', 'The Long Shadow' (both ITV) and the last three seasons of 'Brassic' (Sky) as well as upcoming TV shows 'The Blame' (ITV) and 'The Split Up' (BBC).

In addition to her work with Sonia, Leila has provided casting assistance to Shaheen Baig Casting on productions such as 'The Gallows Pole' (BBC) and, most recently 'Adolescence' (Netflix).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us at: theauditionpals@gmail.com 

Here are the links to our free platform for Actors. Never pay or struggle for a read in for your auditions again! Join us if not on the platform already! 

https://www.facebook.com/share/g/1DXYi988sL/?mibextid=wwXIfr

https://www.instagram.com/theauditionpal?igsh=aGNoYm92dnJxZmM4&utm_source=qr

Hopefully see you very soon! 

TAP Team

items.text:
An actor was just asking how to start. I thought I'd post the answer I gave him here. 

Just in case anyone else has the same question.  

Classes are the place to start. 

Once you get into classes you'll meet people who can help you but here are a few things you can do right away. 

1. Think of your self as a professional right away. Get a schedule together for your practice time. 

Read scripts. 

Think of the movies you like and google them plus screenplay, you should find them. 

Professionals read full scripts so start doing that. 

2. Have a look at yourself in the mirror and think about which actors you share a look with. Many actors want to be cast in an action hero role when they look like the sidekick. 

If that's the case (not saying it is - just an example) you need to live like an action hero actor. That means the food and workout routines and practicing those kinds of scenes. 

3. Learn the craft. Get really good at both acting and auditioning. They are 2 separate beasts. 

You know when you see a shitty actor on screen and you think, "I would be so much better." 

They're probably great at auditioning. So learn them both.

Hope this helps. 

We have a free class every Tuesday at 12:30 pm pacific. Message me for the link if you'd like to join us.

Did you and your partner meet online?

Salt & Lime Media is casting REAL COUPLES who met on the dating apps for an upcoming campaign. If this sounds like you, we’d love to hear your stories.

Adults (18+) are welcome to apply. All genders, sexualities and backgrounds are encouraged.

What we are looking for:

•⁠  ⁠Real couples who met on the dating apps

•⁠  ⁠You’re up for being on camera and sharing your story'

If this sounds like you, submit your story here for a chance to be featured in our next campaign, filming in March and will require **travel to the US**. 

Apply Here:[ https://forms.gle/3JznSrqLFhAgnE5s8](https://forms.gle/3JznSrqLFhAgnE5s8)

Participants who are selected will be compensated and all travel costs covered. 

Standard background checks apply if you’re shortlisted.

Please be assured that all the information you share with us in your submission remains confidential. You can read more about our Talent Privacy Policy here:[ https://saltandlimemedia.com/creator-talent-privacy-policy/](https://saltandlimemedia.com/creator-talent-privacy-policy/)

Weekly Wins!

Come on then, what’s been your little victory this week? 🎬

Maybe you landed an audition, nailed a self-tape, finally updated your headshots, or just made it through Monday without swearing at the universe.

Big or small, every win counts, drop yours in the comments and let’s give each other a bit of well earned applause. 👏🎬🇬🇧

Maybe you landed an audition, nailed a self-tape, finally updated your headshots, or just made it through Monday without swearing at the universe.

Big or small, every win counts, drop yours in the comments and let’s give each other a bit of well earned applause. 👏🎬🇬🇧

items.text:
**Szukam modelki na zasadzie TFP Gliwice/Katowice ( Śląsk )**

Szukam pań które nie krępują się własnego ciała i chciałaby mieć ciekawą pamiątkę w postaci klimatycznych zdjęć. Wiem jak bardzo jest ważna akceptacja własnego ciała bo przez to też możemy inaczej funkcjonować. Przez takie zdjęcia można również tego dokonać. Sesja w głównej mierze jest jako taki motywator.

 

Poszukuje kobiety w **wieku od 25 **lat nie koniecznie z doświadczeniem pozowania, na zasadach Tfp mieszkającej w Gliwicach lub okolicach Zabrze czy Katowice najdalej. Posiadam na wyposażeniu mini studio z kilkoma tłami oraz lampami. Mam również duży wybór kostiumów i gadżetów do wykorzystywania. Główny motyw do kobieta: Piękna i drapieżna! Sama sesja trwa przeważnie od 1,5h do 2h w zalezności od motywów.

** **

**Temat 1 – ‘’Kobieta mafii 1930’’**

Postać kobiety osadzona w 1930 roku w roli bogatej kobiety, która trudni się gangsterstwem. Przewidziane są ujęcia m.in. przy stoliku na którym są pieniądze, wino, rewolwer. Tło jest wydrukowane w formie muru, cegieł. Motyw sensualny.

** **

**Temat 2 – ‘’Wampirzyca w baroku 1700’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana najpierw w suknie czarną oraz peleryne z kapturem. Do tego czarna długa peruka oraz czarne paznokcie. W kolejnym etapie sesji motyw sensualny.

** **

**Temat 3 – ‘’Duchy lasu’’**

Postać kobiety ubrana w wianek i w pelerynę z otwartym przodem. W dłoni ma zakrwawiony sierp. Usta czarne oraz paznokcie.

** **

**Temat 4 – ‘’Kleopatra’’**

Postać kobiety z czarna peruką w stylu Kleopatry. W prawej recę trzymac będzie berło Anubisa a w drugiej ręcę księgę umarłych. Na biodrach będzie mieć jedynie klasyczne odzienie z 2 części. Na klatce piersiowej założony będzie napierśnik złoty.

** **

**Temat 5 – ‘’Odważna Piratka ‘’**

Postać kobiety ubrana w strój piracki: kamizelka, koszula, kapelusz, spodnie i kapelusz a do tego rekwizyty pistolet czy kufel piwa.

https://www.maxmodels.pl/lukus_wielki2

** **

**Zapraszam na stronę**

** **

**Facebook Łukasz Magiera – Fotografia**

www.instagram.com/lukasz.magiera.official

Więcej informacji na Priv

items.text:
Poszukujemy ZAWODOWYCH AKTORÓW/EK, STUDENTÓW/EK AKTORSTWA I BARDZO ZDOLNYCH AMATORÓW/EK do serialu kryminalnego realizowanego we Wrocławiu.

ROLE:

1. Jurek (35l.) - 13,22,27.01, 12.02 - życiowy nieudacznik z przerośniętym ego – typowy „macho w kapciach”

2. Emilka (30l.) - 13,22,27.01 - pracuje w salonie fryzjerskim 

3. Damian (27l.) - 14,20,23.01 - łagodny i ugodowy chłopak

4. Jagoda (13l.) - 14,20,23.01 - Spokojna i introwertyczna, ale potrafi się też postawić, gdy jest pewna swojej racji.

4. Tobiasz (16l.) - 14,20,23.01 - Brat Jagody. Szybciej działa niż myśli. Bardzo kocha swoją siostrę i zrobiłby dla niej wszystko. Inteligentny i błyskotliwy,

5. Gracjan (30l.) - 14,20.01 - przyjaciel Patryka i jego straż przyboczna. Prosty chłopak o wielkich mięśniach.

6. Patryk (35l.) - 14,20.01 - Zakapior. Rządził na dzielnicy. Mściwy i podły. Kiedy dziewczyna go rzuciła, zagroził jej,że się zemści.

7. Wiktoria (35l.) - 14,16,23.01, 6.02 - Zniszczona, przeorana przez życie, z marginesu.

8. Marek (45l.) - 14,16,23.01 - Konkubent Wiktorii, ojciec dzieci. Głęboka patologia, damski bokser, człowiek okrutny i odrażający.

9. Kamil (25l.) - 14,16,23.01 - Młody chłopak, typ bad boya, jednak o dobrym sercu. Od lat mieszka w Holandii, gdzie uciekł ze strachu przed odsiadką

10. Bartula (25l.) - 14.01 - Kolega z dawnych lat Kamila, który brał z nim udział w bójce. W przeciwieństwie do Kamila nie zwiał i poniósł konsekwencję

11. Anastazja (18l.) - 16.01, 6.02 - Zwykła nastolatka, przypadkowa świadek.

12. Pajda (54l.) - 15,16.01, 6.02 - Biznesmen, dobroczyńca. Prezes fundacji- Dobry Start. Z lekką nadwagą. Pewny siebie, trochę cwaniaczek. Udaje filantropa. Ma dużo za uszami.

13. Zosia (50l.) - 15.01, 6.02 - żona Pajdy. Zajmuje się mężem i domem. Trochę wycofana, zazdrosna, wścibska. Histeryczka. Mąż jest jej całym światem. 

14. Naczelny (52l.) - 15.01 - naczelny gazety. Konkretny, zawodowiec, profesjonalista. 

15. Strzelecki (65l.) - 16.01 - emerytowany detektyw

Zgłoszenia:
[https://forms.gle/ouLpW5nM4MF3tXcDA](https://forms.gle/ouLpW5nM4MF3tXcDA)

lub mailowo
pawel.edwinfilm@gmail.com

- imię i nazwisko 
- data urodzenia 
- wzrost 
- ukończona szkoła aktorska 
- miasto zamieszkania 
- zdjęcia (sylwetka i twarz)
- materiały wideo 

zgłoszenia do bazy (poza postaciami powyżej)
[https://forms.gle/w9m6LxTyT5ouhPU4A](https://forms.gle/w9m6LxTyT5ouhPU4A)

OGŁOSZENIE SKIEROWANE DO OSÓB Z CAŁEJ POLSKI!

ZAPEWNIAMY NOCLEG ORAZ ZWROT KOSZTÓW PODRÓŻY!

Odezwiemy się do wybranych osób.

Proszę o nie wysyłanie informacji na PRIV oraz o nie zgłaszanie się pod postem.

ZAPRASZAMY!

Agencja Aktorska EDWIN FILM.

message.text:
Online Camera Acting Intensive
Film, Television & Digital Media

Galbeni Culture’s Online Camera Acting Intensive is a professional training program designed for actors who want to confidently work in film, television, commercials, and digital media.

Starting January 19, this intensive offers structured, practical training focused on on-camera performance, audition technique, and the realities of the acting industry.

What You Will Study:
 • Camera Acting for Film & Television
 • Acting & Scene Study
 • Audition Technique for the Camera
 • Sitcom & Commercial Acting
 • Voice & Speech
 • Movement & Improvisation
 • Musical Theatre & Singing
 • Social Media Content Creation for Actors
 • The Business of Acting

Program Details:
 • 📍 Online (Live via Microsoft Teams)
 • 🗓 Monday – Friday
 • ⏱ 4–6 hours per day
 • 👤 Ages 16+
 • 🎓 Suitable for beginners to intermediate actors

Tuition:
 • Early Bird: €990
 • Regular: €1,190
 • Young Talent (16–21): €850
 • Payment plans available

🎬 Build confidence.
🎬 Master the camera.
🎬 Prepare for real auditions.

#acting #actingschool #actingclass #actorslife #onlineclasses

items.text:
I’m currently casting for an UK Equity short film via Spotlight. This is not my first time casting, but it has been a while (submissions are closed FYI, please don’t message me about it).

We received 940 submissions for two roles. Quite overwhelming. Understandable given our industry right now. Only 200 of subs were from self-repped actors, which surprised me given it was sent to all.

Giving each submission just one minute of attention is nearly 17 hours without a break. Days of work. When numbers are this high, long listing is about finding easy reasons to say yes / no.

I had to quickly reduce 940 to around 200. And then the director and I created a long list of 40 who were invited tape. 14 of which declined to tape / were unavailable. I would love to give feedback to actors individually on why they didn’t progress, sometimes it’s something so simple to rectify. But there’s just no time.

This most recent foray into casting has really given me some insight that will shape how I think about my own acting CV and representation. I wonder if my experience might help others in a very broad sense, because I was honestly shocked by how basics were not being met, by performers, and also agents.

I’m considering doing some sort of social media series to explain what made people stand out at various stages, and more crucially what basic things might be corrected.

If this is something you’re interested in, or you want to stay updated, you are welcome to follow me on Instagram. I am easy to find. I will be casting more projects in 2026, including my own work.

Happy New Year everyone. I’ve seen so much talent over the past few weeks, please know that even if you didn’t tape for me, I looked carefully at every single CV I was sent, and will remember those who stood out.

topComments.text:
Insight is always appreciated 👍
Back in the late 1990’s I was working with a touring theatre company and in my third season with them was given the opportunity to direct a production of The Tempest, and was involved in the casting process for that and the company’s other production of As You Like It.

During that I gained a huge insight into my own practices and choices as an actor, from application to presentation to performance.

I took a break from the industry in 2010 when I got married and chose a different, and frankly more financially stable, industry until my daughter was older.

It wasn’t a hard choice to make, my career path had been narrowing down for awhile at that stage, but I was eventually nudged back into the industry.

Everything was different, instead of printed cv’s and (expensive to reproduce) 8x10 headshots, all applications were made online, my then 14 year old daughter was having to show me how to operate a computer.

Spotlight was different, no longer these great tomes that one could peruse in order to find a (overpriced) photographer for your headshots and hope that a casting director went to when they needed a new face, but an opportunity to profile oneself and direct appropriate jobs directly to one’s email.

Any and all insight into improving my search for work is always welcome.

I have a very good agent who regularly communicates with me, the best that I’ve ever had.

I’m still ambitious, I’m still struggling to make ends meet, but I’m happy and healthy as I approach my 60th birthday in the autumn of 2026.

I’ll follow you on instagram 👍

Thanks for posting this. An interesting post, which reminds me just how competitive this industry is. I’d be interested to know the playing ages of the roles you were casting. I was surprised to read that a large number declined to tape. Others could have had the opportunity. Also that the basics were ignored - presumably these were self tape instructions etc. The industry is so very competitive and it is increasingly difficult to book jobs, but the least we can ALL (whatever our individual role in the process) do is be professional, communicate well, submit self tapes on time, be clear with instructions, follow instructions etc. That is the job and I’ve heard many say that we should view the audition as an acting job in itself. By the way, I’m following you on IG.

"CAESAR: The Ides of March" is currently shaping up to be a full feature film that will be released this year 2026.
We are currently getting ready to film the last scene this month that should bring the total runtime of this film to the 1hr 20min mark and we will submit this to the Edinburgh International Film festival upon its completion. This has been 5 years in the making starting back in 2020.

Currently being supported by Boathouse Pictures in the USA, this film encompasses both short films back to back for a full cinematic experience.

The next time you hear from us. This will be a fully finished first feature film.

Peace

Gods and warriors collide in this modern retelling of history’s greatest battle. At the intimate Lyric Hyperion, a war-weary poet tells us the story of our fascination with war and asks the question: how do you know when you’ve won? 

Starring Madison Uphoff and directed by Morgan McKinnis, AN ILIAD conquers the Lyric Hyperion on January 23 and 24.

Stick around after the performance for craft drinks and to connect with fellow LA artists and theater-goers.

Tickets on sale now on Eventbrite: [http://bit.ly/49NLp3R](http://bit.ly/49NLp3R)

items.text:
Cześć, mam na imię Kornelia, rocznikowo mam 17 lat. Aktorstwo to mój głos serca i kierunek, który czuję w sobie od zawsze, dlatego chciałabym spróbować swoich sił w castingach i realnie rozwijać się w tym kierunku.

Jestem osobą bardzo energiczną, ciekawą ludzi i emocji, momentami zakręconą i spontaniczną. Naturalnie ciągnie mnie do ról intensywnych, psychologicznych, dramatycznych czy mrocznych, ale jednocześnie chętnie sprawdzę się także w rolach lżejszych, pozytywnych i wesołych, ponieważ zależy mi na różnorodności i zdobywaniu doświadczenia.

Mam 165–167 cm wzrostu. Aktualnie mam niebieskie włosy z fioletowym pasemkiem oraz kolczyk w wardze i brwi, jednak jestem otwarta na zmiany wizerunku i dostosowanie wyglądu do potrzeb roli.

Mam za sobą udział w Miss Polska, gdzie dotarłam do etapu ćwierćfinałowego, co dało mi doświadczenie sceniczne, kontakt z kamerą oraz pracę pod presją.

Nie posiadam jeszcze dużego doświadczenia aktorskiego, ale mam ogromną motywację, wyobraźnię, odwagę do próbowania i chęć nauki. Każdą szansę traktuję jako możliwość rozwoju.
Zdjęcia oraz dodatkowe informacje chętnie prześlę w wiadomości prywatnej.

items.text:
# Method Acting Grundkurs
Beginn Mittwoch, 14. Januar 2026
[Sichere dir jetzt einen Kursplatz!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)
**Du willst:**

· die Schauspielmethode lernen, die sich in den letzten 100 Jahren weltweit durchgesetzt hat

· echt, authentisch, glaubwürdig, wahrhaftig, berührend und bewegend spielen

· deinen einzigartigen Weg zur Figur finden

· dich in Gefühle und Zustände einer Rolle hineinversetzen können

· deine Atmung und Stimme entwickeln

· deine Körpersprache in einer motivierten Gruppe von Gleichgesinnten entwickeln

· organisch die Objektarbeit in dein Schauspiel integrieren

· lernen, wie man effektiv und effizient Texte auswendig lernt

· deine mentale Stärke aufbauen

· die bewährten Kursunterlagen erhalten und dich von ausgesuchten Videobeispielen inspirieren lassen

· 24 Stunden praktische Erfahrung sammeln

· ein Teilnahmezertifikat erhalten

· von mehr als 40 Jahren Berufserfahrung profitieren

[Dann ist dieser Kurs genau das richtige für DICH!](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Und das sagen Teilnehmer*innen:

„Auf jeden Fall wird meine Reise bei Dir weiter gehen. Ich bin begeistert, wie Du förderst und forderst und uns dabei hilfst, den nächsten Schritt zu wagen und zu gehen.“ I.

„Hallo Marco, ich profitiere noch immer von deinem Kurs im Playbacktheater *, in dem ich seit etwa 10 Jahren dabei bin.“ H.

„Herzlichen Dank an dich für den belebenden und lehrreichen Kurs, sowie deine Offenheit.“ E.

„Mir macht der Method Acting Kurs grosse Freude, die individuelle Arbeit gefällt mir sehr.“ S.

„heute erlebt und umgesetzt. … einfach spannend bei dir im unterricht. jedes wort stimmt. danke marco.“ R.

„Danke für den interessanten Kurs. Ich lerne viel und bin auch froh, um die gute Dokumentation, die uns zu Verfügung steht.“ D.

„Übrigens, ich habe die Stunde letztes Mal super gefunden – ich kam todmüde an und ging wacher und selbstbewusster nach Hause. Danke dafür!“ A.

„Erst mal Danke das Du mich aus der Komfortzone herausgeholt hast, dein Kurs war sehr hilfreich.“ P.

„Your training helped, Marco. A teammate told me it was „like real method acting“. I told them I took method acting. They didn’t know that when hiring me.“ A.

(Die Testimonials sind aus Datenschutzgründen anonymisiert. Du willst noch mehr Testimonials? Dann lese auf der [Website](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) und auf Google weiter.)

Du willst es genau wissen. Auf der Website findest du alles, was du brauchst:

• Alle [Details](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/) zum Kurs

• [Testimonials / Bewertungen](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

• Die [Anmeldung](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

[Was hält dich auf?](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Kursleitung: Marco Hausammann-Gilardi hat mehr als 40 Jahre Erfahrung als Schauspieler, Autor, Regisseur und Produzent in Theater, Film und Fernsehen. Er war von 1986 bis 1988 an Strasberg’s Real Stage, bei Ernie Martin (Artistic Director Actor’s Studio Los Angeles) und am Actor’s Studio New York (PO). Seit 1988 unterrichtet er auf dieser Basis und seinen praktischen Berufserfahrungen. Er ist Mitglied folgender Berufsverbände:

• t. Theaterschaffende der Schweiz/Professionnels du spectacle Suisse/Professionisti dello spettacolo Svizzera

• Verband Filmregie und Drehbuch Schweiz ARF/FDS

• Verband für Film- und Fernsehdramaturgie e.V. VeDRA

[ZES Zentrum für Entwicklung im Schauspiel](https://zes-info.ch/grundkurs-method-acting/)

Das Kompetenzzentrum für Method Acting

🎬 **VIPER – CODE RED**
*Internationale Action-Serie im Kinostil*

Für unser **produktionsreifes Serienprojekt** **VIPER – CODE RED** suchen wir **zeitgleich**:

➡️ eine **Top-Produktionsfirma**
➡️ ein **vollständiges professionelles Filmsetup**
➡️ einen **starken Streaming-Partner**
(z. B. Amazon Prime Video / Paramount+)

👉 Kein Frühstadium. Kein Konzept. **Wir sind bereit für Umsetzung.**

✔ **Drehbuch vollständig fertiggestellt**
✔ Exposé & Pitchdeck abgeschlossen
✔ **Vollständige Kostenaufstellung / Kalkulation vorhanden**

  – Prag
  – Italien
  – Tschechien
✔ Realistisches Action-Setting – **keine Sci-Fi- oder Fantasie-Tech**

Wir suchen **kein Einzelgewerk**, sondern ein **eingespieltes, professionelles Gesamtsetup**, inkl.:

🔹 Produktion / Line Production
🔹 Regie & Regieorganisation
🔹 Kamera · Licht · Grip
🔹 Ton / Set-Ton / Post-Sound
🔹 Szenenbild · Ausstattung · Requisite
🔹 Produktionsleitung & Set-Management
🔹 Postproduktion (Schnitt, Grading, Tonmischung)
🔹 International tauglicher Workflow

👉 **Keine lose Crew. Kein Improvisieren. Nur Profis mit Referenzen.**

🔹 Erfahrung in Serie / Film / Action / Drama
🔹 Klare Strukturen & belastbarer Workflow
🔹 Langfristige Planungskompetenz
🔹 **Partnerschaft auf Augenhöhe** (keine reine Dienstleistung)

## 📺 **GESUCHT – STREAMING-PARTNER**

🔹 Hochwertiger Serien-Content
🔹 Mehrstaffelige Auswertung
🔹 Internationale Perspektive
🔹 Character-Driven Action mit klarer Handschrift

👉 Ziel: **stabile, langfristige Zusammenarbeit** – kein Einmal-Deal.

✔ Klare Zuständigkeiten
✔ Professionelles Arbeitsumfeld

❗ Keine Hobby-Mentalität
❗ Keine Ego-Shows
❗ **Nur professionelle Partner**

CASTING CALL – Role of “Beck” (Paid + IMDb Credit) — Becoming Our Spider-Man Fan Film🎬

Hi everyone!
We’re currently casting for a fan film titled Becoming Our Spider-Man, and we’re looking for a talented young actor to play Beck, an important emotional role in the story.

Role: Beck

Age Range: 11–13

Gender: Female

Character Type: Tough exterior, but dealing with pressure and self-doubt underneath. Beck has a powerful emotional moment with Miles (Spider-Man), where he helps her calm down and feel safe.

We’re looking for someone with strong emotional range, especially the ability to portray vulnerability in a grounded, realistic way.

About the Scene

Beck’s storyline is a key moment for Miles’ character. It shows his empathy and responsibility as Spider-Man, and Beck’s performance helps carry the emotional weight of that moment.
(Everything will be filmed safely, respectfully, and with a guardian present.)

Compensation

Paid role

IMDb credit provided

If you’re interested in the role ￼ please send your headshot to my email

 📧 @ppeterb954@gmail.com
￼
(And no for those who are asking this is not a scam)

items.text:
**012  Mini serial  wojenny 1940 – Szukamy ojca głównej bohaterki ( casting on-line )**

 

Nasza Gliwicka Grupa Pasjonatów ‘’Grupa1940’’ poszukuje mężczyzny do roli ojca głównej bohaterki. Najlepiej jakby kandydat miałby od **40 – 45 lat** o rudych włosach i bez zarostu, o określonych parametrach: **obwód w klatce 100- 105, obwód pasa 90/95 cm** i **wzrost: 175 -180** . Szukamy kogoś **z Gliwic lub okolic: Zabrze, Katowice** najdalej. Postać ta będzie nosić mundur polski podporucznika.Same zdjęcia będą realizowane na terenie Gliwic. Niestety nie zwracamy kosztów podróży. Postać mężczyzny pojawi się w pierwszym odcinku i zostanie zabita przez odział niemiecki. Pojawi się też w retrospekcji bitwy w 1919 roku z Bolszewikami gdzie zostanie ranny w nogę. Oczywiście mile widziane doświadczenie pracy z tekstem. Scenę wstępnie będziemy realizować na przełomie marca lub kwietnia.

 

**Na wiosnę roku 2026 planujemy realizacje zdjęc do tego **projektu. Będziemy realizować mini serial oparty o wątki grupy okultystycznej ’’**Ahnenerbe’**’ która chce zdobyć słynne artefakty ale w tym ktoś im chce przeszkadzać. Projekt będzie  się składać z 6 odcinków po 10/12 minut każdy. Będziemy też sukcesywnie dodawać inne ogłoszenia związane z tym projektem. Mile widziane zdjęcia aktualne. Na zdjęciu powyżej osoba będzie mieć podobny kostium.** **Umieszczone materiały są z naszej sesji.** Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Od 01.04.25 założyliśmy swój kanał na portalu youtube z filmami z naszych planów żeby można było zobaczyć jak to u nas wygląda od kuchni. 

 

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCE8KyfwpyFGzzwUDqdwy74g

 

**Nie będzie to zlecenie płatne.**

 

Więcej informacji na Priv

**Serial nie jest stworzony z sympatii do tej nazistowskiej organizacji lecz wynika to z samego scenariusza aby ukazał zbrodnie i sam fakt iż była w pełni zła. W produkcji znajdą się osoby, które będą chcieć walczyć i potępiać te wielkie zło jakim był nazizm. W oparciu o Dz.U.2017.0.2204 t.j. - Ustawa z dnia 6 czerwca 1997 r. - Kodeks karny,Art. 256 "Propagowanie faszyzmu lub innego ustroju totalitarnego lub nawoływanie domnienawiści", §3 - nie narusza prawa proponując przedmiot do celów historycznych lub kolekcjonerskich.**

TEATR ME/ST 
CASTING dla aktorów z Warszawy.
Zapraszamy do udziału w castingu (zrobienie zastępstwa) w spektaklu „Stosunki Prawne”.
Poszukujemy aktora (mężczyzny) w wieku ok. 40–55 lat.
Spektakl jest dwuosobowy i był grany w TEATRZE ME/ST w latach 2014-2021. 

Prosimy o przygotowanie:
• krótkiej wizytówki aktorskiej (do 2 min nagrania video).
Wizytówka powinna zawierać:
• kilku zdań o sobie,
• informację o wykształceniu i doświadczeniu teatralnym.

Nagranie prosimy umieścić na YouTube i przesłać link na adres:
mest.teatr@gmail.com

Informacje organizacyjne:
Skontaktujemy się w wybranymi osobami – wtedy prześlemy teksty na II etap castingu.

Drugi etap odbędzie się między 6 a 10 stycznia. 

Uwaga – mamy już ustalone najbliższe terminy pokazów spektaklu:
• 22 lutego (Warszawa)
• 8 marca (spektakl wyjazdowy)
Dostępność w obu terminach jest warunkiem koniecznym udziału w castingu.

Próby będą się odbywały w różnych porach dnia – dostosowanych do możliwości czasowych zespołu. 

W internecie można znaleźć informacje o spektaklu oraz trailer. 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Qro-Xj5mmJY

sharedPost.text:
Join Us!
We are honored to bring onboard to The Broadway Mentors Program, Emmy nominated Voice Over Director/Director Benjie Randall who will be conducting this very fun and extraordinarily informative class via Zoom. 

Only up to 10 participants. Ages 14 up - Adults 

Jan 21st
6:30-8:30 pm EST
All materials will be supplied
$165

To register: https://www.broadwaymentorsprogram.com/master-classes

BIO
Benjie Randall (he/him) is an Emmy-nominated Voice Over Director and Casting Director, recognized for his work on the recently released Wonder Pets in the City for Apple TV+ and
Nickelodeon. 

He graduated from The Boston Conservatory with a BFA in Musical Theater and a concentration in Directing. After several years performing in New York musical theater, Benjie landed the voice role of Chumpkins—the tech-savvy pig—on Disney Jr.’s animated original series P. King Duckling. He
soon expanded into Casting and Directing for the series, eventually becoming the Assistant Voice Over Director while continuing to voice the principal character.

Benjie then transitioned fully into Voice Over Direction within children’s media. He Cast and Directed Hulu’s original series The Bravest Knight, which featured an impressive lineup of talent
including Wanda Sykes, RuPaul, Wilson Cruz, T.R. Knight, Christine Baranski, Jazz Jennings, and others. The Bravest Knight went on to win the 2020 GLAAD Media Award for Outstanding Kids and Family Programming.

He has since contributed to several Netflix original series, including Dee and Friends in Oz, The Sneetches, and Karma’s World—created by Chris “Ludacris” Bridges. Karma’s World has
received three NAACP Image Award nominations as well as an Emmy nomination.

❗️Dringend❗️
Casting-Aufruf – Schauspieler gesucht, 18–20 Jahre im Raum Stuttgart (Umgebung)

Logline: Ein unsicherer Lehrer, der vergeblich um Respekt kämpft, wird durch den Spott seiner Schüler so radikal verändert, dass er vom Gutmütigen zum gnadenlosen Strengen mutiert. 

Für einen Diploma-Kurzfilm (ca. 6–7 Minuten) im Genre Komödie suche ich sehr kurzfristig einen männlichen 

Schauspieler im Spielalter 18–20 Jahre für eine Nebenrolle mit Text. Drehtage sind am 14.01.26 und 15.01.26.

Die Rolle ist die eines Schülers. Der Textumfang ist überschaubar und umfasst ca. vier Sätze.

Leider hat die ursprünglich zugesagte Besetzung unerwartet kurzfristig abgesagt, weshalb ich nun zeitnah einen passenden Darsteller suche.

Rahmenbedingungen:

• Low-Budget-Produktion (Diplomfilm)

• Vergütung im Low-Budget-Bereich

• Fahrtkosten werden erstattet

Ich freue mich über schnelle Rückmeldungen und kurze Bewerbungen (gern mit Foto/Showreel, falls vorhanden).

Bewerbung bitte per E-Mail!

Kontakt: Bianca Brandner 

                brandner.bianca@web.de

items.text:
Darsteller für atmosphärischen Filmtrailer gesucht!

Hallo an alle! Für einen Proof-of-Concept (POC)
Trailer mit intensiver spanischer Stimmung suche ich einen ausdrucksstarken Mann, der Lust hat, ein besonderes Projekt mit zum Leben zu erwecken.

Wen ich suche:
• Du hast einen südeuropäischen / mediterranen Look.
• Du kannst dich sehr gut bewegen zu Latin Musik und hast ein gutes Körpergefühl.          •hast Lust auf ein kreatives Projekt mit viel Leidenschaft und Rhythmus.
Zum Projekt:

Wir drehen einen Tanz-PoC , den wir bei internationalen Festivals einreichen werden. Das Ziel ist es, aus diesem POC ein großeres Filmprojekt zu entwickeln. Das ist eine super Chance für deine Sichtbarkeit.

Da es ein No-Budget-Herzensprojekt ist, gibt es keine Gage, aber:
Wir übernehmen deine Reisekosten.
Es gibt volle Verpflegung am Set.
Sichtbarkeit bei Festivals.

Hast du Lust auf spanische Vibes und eine tolle Zusammenarbeit? Dann schreib mir gerne eine Nachricht mit Foto oder einem kurzen Video über mediterran-film@web.de .

Ich freue mich auf dich !

message.text:
SONGS FROM LIFE – 10.01.2026
Gesang, der berührt. Geschichten, die verwandeln.
Deutschlandpremiere

Adresse: Gallus Theater, Kleyerstr.15, 60326 Frankfurt, T:758060-20
Ticketverkauf:  https://www.gallustheater.de/prog/vob.php?i=4

Die preisgekrönte Sängerin Stefanie Rummel nimmt das Publikum mit auf eine fesselnde musikalische Reise – von den Pariser Cafés über die Berliner Kabarettbühnen bis in die Clubs Manhattans.
Mit Songs im Stil von Piaf, Weill, Sondheim und eigenen Kompositionen erzählt sie von besonderen Momenten des Lebens – voller Sehnsucht, Humor, Warmherzigkeit und Tiefe.
Als „herzberührend“ und mit „brillanter Bühnenpräsenz“ gefeiert, begeistert sie ihr Publikum in den USA, Großbritannien und ganz Europa – und geht nächstes Jahr erneut in Australien auf Tournee.

★★★★ „Herausragende Stimme“ – TheReviewHub
★★★★ „Eine Offenbarung“ – LondonTheatre1
Ein inspirierendes, berührendes musikalisches Cabaret über das Leben – getragen von Liedern, Persönlichkeit und Storytelling.

items.text: This is clowning in another level. The connection with the audience,,,, Don't miss this rare opportunity to work with Suzy Ferguson, who is brilliant and doesn't run workshops for freelancers that often. I highly recommend her workshop.

sharedPost.text:
𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗣𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿 𝗼𝗳 𝗖𝗼𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻:  𝗮𝗻 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗿𝗼 𝘁𝗼 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗿𝗮𝗽𝗲𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗹 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 | 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗦𝘂𝘇𝗶𝗲 𝗙𝗲𝗿𝗴𝘂𝘀𝗼𝗻 | 𝟮𝟵-𝟯𝟭 𝗝𝗮𝗻 𝟮𝟲 | 𝗟𝗼𝗻𝗱𝗼𝗻, 𝗨𝗞
This wonderful workshop with Suzie Ferguson (formally Director of Hearts and Minds Clown Doctors in Scotland) is a process of discovery that invites you to connect with your authenticity and playfulness, to discover how you can be more yourself, more truthful in a moment of connection with other people.

You don’t need a clowning background, just curiosity, openness, and a readiness to be active in exploring what connection means for you. It is open to anyone who connects with others in their work: teachers, directors, therapists, priests, health workers, those who work in music, art and theatre, as well as clowns who work in social/therapeutic contexts. 
This process is experienced practically through guided exercises, working alone, in pairs and as a group. It is not about finding your clown or refining a performance piece; it is about helping you find what you need to learn about connection for your practice.
Suzie teaches Applied Clowning, a form of clowning that extends beyond the stage, into the world.
Suzie works internationally and is well-loved for her practical, supportive and freeing approach to teaching therapeutic clowning with participants from varied professional backgrounds.
𝗙𝗼𝗿 𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝗳𝗼𝗿𝗺, 𝗲𝗺𝗮𝗶𝗹: 𝘄𝗵𝘆𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗶𝘁𝘂𝘁𝗲@𝗮𝗼𝗹.𝗰𝗼𝗺
𝗗𝗲𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗹𝘀 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗪𝗵𝘆 𝗡𝗼𝘁 𝗪𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗖𝗹𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗦𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗼𝗹 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟲 𝗰𝗼𝘂𝗿𝘀𝗲𝘀: https://thewhynotinstitute.com/when-are-the-courses/

items.text:
Open theatre auditions coming up at The South Devon Players Theatre & Film Company, Brixham

DEVON/ OPEN BOOK PROFITSHARE / THEATRE / ANY GENDER OR ETHNICITY/

- Roles open for actors aged 16 to the sky's the limit. 

- A lot of the roles in our staging of this play  are not bound by gender; we are looking for the strongest actor for each roles. 

- Any ethnicity/ accent/ experience level equally welcome. What we are looking for are great performance skills, pleasant friendly teamwork, and the desire to be an active part of a really excellent quality show. 

- The show is set in 1793. The show is suitable for all audiences. 

- Period costumes made and supplied for all cast. 

- if you cannot make auditions on January 25th please contact us to arrange an audition over the two weeks before. 

- Actors should be based in, or have a base in, Devon because of attending rehearsals and performances. Sorry none of us who are regulars with the theatre team are in a financial or housing position to be able to put people up from further afield. We have a performance in London but have a minibus fundraised for, to get people there and back to Devon. 

- Our show teams are diverse in terms of age, experience, ethnicity and we usually have several neurodivergent team members - everyone coming on board should be willing to work as a part of a diverse group of people. 

- the show is profitshare for funding reasons. We cover rehearsal space/ costumes/ insurance etc by selling second hand bits on eBay and handmade jewellery in a couple of local shops.  This is on an open book process where ticket sales reports and any venue hire costs are shown upfront for perusal, and the ticket profits (Ticket sales less performance venue hire) are shared equally between each person in the show team. Sadly we cannot guarantee how much this is as it can vary wildly as is dependant on ticket sales. We constantly do our best to both promote the show to get those sales as high as possible and to apply for funding to bring everyone up to equity rates but this cant be guaranteed and we don’t believe in promising what we can’t guarantee to deliver. 

- ALL cast and crew also are given  access to portfolio photos and show video, copies of any press or promotional content featuring themselves, references on request (after completion of their first show run with us), and anything else that we find we can offer. 

- and - in answer to a common question we get:  nobody is ever charged anything to audition or perform with us.

Do please drop us a line with any questions not answered here or in the downloadable audition resources.

CONGRATS TO OUR SCRIPT COMPETITION WINNERS!!! 🎥 After receiving over 90 script submissions and trying to narrow it down to our Top 3, our creator and head producer decided to pick THREE MORE scripts for our team to direct, produce, and release as part of the upcoming Callbacks Competition series — 6 short films in 6 months, all featuring Austin-based writers, talent, and crew! 

The process:

Our team will hold a casting call for each project (be on the lookout for announcements!), go through a 2 round pre-screening process, and then invite the Top 6 actors to our Callbacks Competition TV show. 🎬 

From there, we will film 3 episodes where our talent will go through the final rounds of a rigorous callback process and audition sides from that month’s script.  The winner will be awarded the lead role, a cash prize, and then step on set with us the following week to make that film! 🏆 🎞️

We are looking for expecting mothers! 

A continuing TV drama series is looking to cast newborn babies due January 2026.

Filming is due to begin from mid February onwards, so parents will need good availability during this period. The exact filming schedule is still to be confirmed.

Both boys and girls can be considered at this stage.

To match the on-screen parents, production are looking for mixed-race babies with one Caucasian parent and one parent of African or Caribbean heritage.

Applicants must live within one hour of BBC Elstree (WD6 1NL) and must be available for a first stage meet on the morning of Thursday 8 January.

Please send the following details to 👉🏻 Talia@daisyanddukes.com with the subject line Newborn Casting 2026:

Parent full name
Postcode
Contact number and email
To help us match the on-screen family, please include:
Baby’s gender (if known)
Due date
Parents’ ethnicities
Clear photos of both parents

Serious applicants only. 

Applications without the required details cannot be considered.

items.text:
# **CASTING CALLS - Student film - Paid**

—

Hi everyone! We are casting for our final-year film at the University of Hertfordshire. 

Title: Hangman

Genre: Horror, Thriller

Shooting Period: **7th - 22nd** **February 2026** (around 5 days)

Locations: **London, Cambridge,** (/ any other areas nearby)

Pay Rate: **£100-200** per day (w/ meal & mileage

allowances according to the **Equity** guideline)

—

Story:

Ethan, a gambling addict drowning in debt and chased by loan sharks. While his family fall apart, he steals his daughter Emma’s tuition money for a last-ditch gamble. He ends up losing everything. Broke and haunted by the mysterious Hangman, a manifestation of his guilt and destruction. Ethan breaks into his own home to steal more money, only to be taken toward a deadly showdown on a quiet road.

—

Lead Roles:

Ethan ** (Male, 35 - 50)**

Bella **(Female, 35 - 50)**

Emma **(Female, 18 - 22)**

(Please check the pictures below for more details.)

—

Supporting Roles:

THE HANGMAN** (Any Gender & Age 18+)**
* Tall is preferred for an imposing presence.
* Will be hidden under a large black cloak and a mask.

Loan Shark 1 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Should look like someone who spends time on the street, maybe with tattoos or a strong build

Loan Shark 2 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Different from Loan Shark 1 to show contrast.

— 

If interested, please send your headshots and resumes to sinfulhangman@gmail.com. All levels of experience are welcome!

For more details, please don't hesitate to contact us through email or our Instagram page (hangman.shortfilms)!

items.summary:
# **CASTING CALLS - Student film - Paid**

—

Hi everyone! We are casting for our final-year film at the University of Hertfordshire. 

Title: Hangman

Genre: Horror, Thriller

Shooting Period: **7th - 22nd** **February 2026** (around 5 days)

Locations: **London, Cambridge,** (/ any other areas nearby)

Pay Rate: **£100-200** per day (w/ meal & mileage

allowances according to the **Equity** guideline)

—

Story:

Ethan, a gambling addict drowning in debt and chased by loan sharks. While his family fall apart, he steals his daughter Emma’s tuition money for a last-ditch gamble. He ends up losing everything. Broke and haunted by the mysterious Hangman, a manifestation of his guilt and destruction. Ethan breaks into his own home to steal more money, only to be taken toward a deadly showdown on a quiet road.

—

Lead Roles:

Ethan ** (Male, 35 - 50)**

Bella **(Female, 35 - 50)**

Emma **(Female, 18 - 22)**

(Please check the pictures below for more details.)

—

Supporting Roles:

THE HANGMAN** (Any Gender & Age 18+)**
* Tall is preferred for an imposing presence.
* Will be hidden under a large black cloak and a mask.

Loan Shark 1 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Should look like someone who spends time on the street, maybe with tattoos or a strong build

Loan Shark 2 **(Male, 25-45)**
* Different from Loan Shark 1 to show contrast.

— 

If interested, please send your headshots and resumes to sinfulhangman@gmail.com. All levels of experience are welcome!

For more details, please don't hesitate to contact us through email or our Instagram page (hangman.shortfilms)!

#studentfilm LOOKING FOR ACTORS! 

NO EXPERIENCE NEEDED

Set in the Edwardian era, England, we follow the short story of a upper class man (CHARLES DAVIES) who’s regular routine is disrupted by a stubborn young English boy (GEORGE) recognises the man and reminds him of the past life he’s been trying to forget.

This is for a student project so there is NO PAY for any of the actors. 

Please share around to people you know, would be lovely to get this casting call about and have many auditions in. 

To apply:

This will be a 1 or 2 day shoot during may/june, specific dates have not been given yet but this project WILL be happening at some point in those months this year. As soon as we get exact dates WE WILL PROVIDE THEM. 

Please share round !!

🎭 CASTING OUVERT
JOB – LA COMÉDIE MUSICALE

Création originale – Œuvre déposée à la SACD

⸻

🔥 LE PROJET

Inspirée du Livre de Job, cette comédie musicale originale raconte l’épreuve d’un homme juste confronté à la perte, au jugement et au silence de Dieu.

Un spectacle intense, incarné, vocalement exigeant, où la voix est au cœur du drame.

⸻

🎤 PROFILS RECHERCHÉS

🔹 CHANTEURS / CHANTEUSES

 • Excellente technique vocale

 • Forte présence scénique

 • Capacité à porter une émotion profonde

 • À l’aise avec une écriture dramatique et spirituelle

Tous âges – Tous profils bienvenus

⸻

🎭 RÔLES PRINCIPAUX

 • JOB – voix masculine puissante (ténor ou baryton clair), grande intensité émotionnelle

 • SATAN (L’ADVERSAIRE) – présence charismatique, voix sombre

 • LA FEMME DE JOB – voix forte, expressive

 • ÉLIFAZ / BILDAD / SOFAR – voix affirmées, personnages de confrontation

 • ENSEMBLE / CHŒUR

⸻

🎶 UNIVERS MUSICAL

 • Pop symphonique

 • Ballades dramatiques

 • Chœurs bibliques

 • Influences latines élégantes

⸻

📍 INFORMATIONS

 • Lieu : Paris

 • Auditions : sur sélection

 • Répétitions : calendrier en cours

 • Statut : création originale

⸻

📩 CANDIDATURE

Envoyer :

 • CV artistique

 • Photo

 • Lien audio ou vidéo (chant)

👉 casting@job-lacomedie-musicale.com

⸻

✨

« Nu je suis sorti du ventre de ma mère,

nu j’y retournerai. »

# **MANDY & BACKSTAGE CASTING CALL: "Shoot Or Run" (coming-of-age drama) **
> ***Amelia runs away, creating new realities and new movies, navigating life as a teenage runaway from an abusive household and confronting self-destruction 🪽***

Hi guys! I am a producer currently on a short film that is in its pre-production stage! Our production is currently casting our main ensemble for our short film. Our **Mandy & Backstage** listing is active and live. If you or others you know who may be interested and would be a good fit for one of the roles, please do not hesitate to apply! 

Lead Roles: Amelia & Noah (Paid) 
Supporting Role: Allan, Daniel (Paid)

Day Player Roles: Young Amelia, Diane (Unpaid)

Check out our Mandy & Backstage listing for more information! 

**BACKSTAGE: **

[https://www.backstage.com/casting/shoot-or-run-3060977/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=casting_call](https://www.backstage.com/casting/shoot-or-run-3060977/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=casting_call)

**MANDY:**

[https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3059775/shoot-or-run-a-coming-of-age-drama/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=casting_call](https://www.mandy.com/aa/project/3059775/shoot-or-run-a-coming-of-age-drama/?utm_source=social_share&utm_medium=copy_link&utm_campaign=casting_call)

If you are unable to put in your interest on our casting platform listings, email me your Headshots, CVs and Showreels at **renee_sugui@hotmail.com**

**Many thanks! **

SHOCKING, CRITICALLY ACCLAIMED  LIVERPOOL STAGEPLAY JANUARY  2026

"I kept fighting for the light..."
Australian actor Georgia Laity stars as  brave and tenacious  University of Tübingen historian, Leonore Siegele-Wenschkewitz.
Leonore's  promising career was cancelled because she blew the whistle on her predecessor at the university, Professor Gerhard Kittel. Leonore proved  Kittel willingly contributed his professional expertise to a foremost Nazi think tank that had been set up to justify the Holocaust.  
Featuring Paul Ryan as Professor Adelbert Stolz.
KITTEL premieres Liverpool Unity January 23rd. Tickets https://www.unitytheatreliverpool.co.uk/.../kittel.../

🦸‍♂️ SUPERHERO JOB ALERT 🦸‍♂️

We’re looking for male performers to play Spiderman and Captain America at children’s parties, events and festivals 🎉

We’ve got a busy run of exciting events coming up and need some new faces to join our lovely team!

This is a really fun job, making kids smile, being silly, bringing the magic, with great pay and a brilliant, supportive team.

✨ What we need from you:

• Confident and happy performing in costume

• Good with kids and not afraid to be a bit daft

• Reliable and trustworthy

• Able to get to Southport (we’re literally 1 minute from Southport train station)

• Weekend availability is important

✨ What you get:

• A genuinely fun job

• Great pay

• Amazing experiences and events

• A lovely team who’ve got your back

If you’ve ever thought “I’d be great as Spiderman”… this might be for you 🕷️😄

📩 Drop us a message if you’re interested and tell us a bit about yourself!

Starkidz Entertainment

Happy New Year Fellow Actors!
We are thrilled to announce our next online casting workshop with the fabulous Leila Ali! 

The workshop will take place 

Saturday February 21st - 10am (GMT) - Zoom

Leila is a Casting Associate for Sonia Allam CDG. 

During her time with Sonia, Leila has worked on various television productions such as 'Better' (BBC), 'Passenger', 'The Long Shadow' (both ITV) and the last three seasons of 'Brassic' (Sky) as well as upcoming TV shows 'The Blame' (ITV) and 'The Split Up' (BBC).

In addition to her work with Sonia, Leila has provided casting assistance to Shaheen Baig Casting on productions such as 'The Gallows Pole' (BBC) and, most recently 'Adolescence' (Netflix).

We are so excited for this one! So DM us on the platform or email us to register interest at: theauditionpals@gmail.com 

Here are the links to our free platform for Actors. Never pay or struggle for a read in for your auditions again! Join us if not on the platform already! 

https://www.facebook.com/share/g/1DXYi988sL/?mibextid=wwXIfr

https://www.instagram.com/theauditionpal?igsh=aGNoYm92dnJxZmM4&utm_source=qr

Hopefully see you very soon! 

TAP Team

🎬 **POLOT MEDIA szuka REŻYSERA CASTINGU / REŻYSERA OBSADY**
📍 **Wrocław | praca stacjonarna**

Szukamy osób do kompletowania obsady do popularnych seriali paradokumentalnych (*Dlaczego Ja*, *Na ratunek 112*, *Trudne Sprawy*).

👉 **Zakres obowiązków:**
* dobór aktorów do produkcji telewizyjnych,
* kontakt z aktorami i uczestnikami,
* rozmowy dotyczące stawek i warunków udziału.

👉 **Wymagania:**
* dyspozycyjność i zaangażowanie,
* umiejętność negocjowania stawek,
* odporność na stres i praca pod presją czasu,
* łatwość w kontakcie z ludźmi.

❗ **Doświadczenie nie jest wymagane.**

🎯 **Oferujemy:**
* elastyczny czas pracy,
* brak dress code’u,
* pracę przy znanych produkcjach TV,
* świetny zespół i realne doświadczenie w branży.

📩 **CV wysyłaj na:** [rekrutacja@polotmedia.pl](mailto:rekrutacja@polotmedia.pl)
Skontaktujemy się z wybranymi osobami.

**🎬 CASTING CALL: *****Illusions of Grandeur ***

******Live Action******

*A Short Film by *Jordan Jackson

**Genre: Drama / Coming-of-Age**

**Tone: Gritty realism with a child’s imaginative lens**

**COMPENSATION: Unpaid :( , Lunch, Copy of Footage **

**Filming Dates: End of January or Early February **

***Please Submit by January 20th, 2025 :)**

**[EMAIL jjacks24@uccs.edu FOR SIDES]**

**LOCATION: Colorado Springs **

**Logline:**

A young boy’s love for his superhero idol blurs with reality when he discovers his hero — and his father — isn’t the savior he imagined.

**🧢 JOEY (6–12)**
**Description:** Innocent, imaginative, and full of heart. Joey escapes his unstable home through superhero fantasies. He believes good always wins — even when the world around him says otherwise.
**Type:** Young actor capable of conveying wonder, playfulness, and heartbreak.

**🌹 ELISE (16–20)**
**Description:** Joey’s older sister and reluctant guardian. She’s grown up too fast — sharp, tired, protective. She carries both resentment and love for her family’s situation.
**Tone:** Grounded realism, emotional restraint with underlying warmth.

**🕯️ JOEY’S MOM (Late 20s–30s)**
**Description:** Overworked and emotionally exhausted. Trying to hold her family together while fighting her own quiet collapse. Her phone calls reveal more than she ever tells her children.
**Type:** Actor who can express fatigue, vulnerability, and quiet strength.

**🥀 GENTLEMAN PERFECT / JAMES (30s–40s)**
**Description:** Once a man of pride and potential — now homeless, addicted, and haunted by his past. In Joey’s eyes, he’s a superhero; in reality, he’s a fallen one. A tragic, layered role requiring depth, subtlety, and broken charisma.
**Tone:** Complex mix of dignity, shame, and fading hope.

**🗝️ HOMELESS MAN (40s–50s)**
**Description:** A street survivor who represents the darker side of desperation. Not evil, but lost. Brief appearance, but a pivotal moment showing Joey’s innocence colliding with danger.

**💔 YOUNG MAN / MUGGER (18–22)**
**Description:** A mirror of what Joey could become — young, broke, trying to survive. His confrontation with Gentleman Perfect reveals both the world’s cruelty and the man’s lingering morality.

**💄 WOMAN (20s–30s)**
**Description:** Victim of the mugging; small role but emotionally grounding. Her scene reinforces Joey’s belief that Gentleman Perfect is still a hero — just before that belief unravels.

**👬 ERIC (18–22)**
**Description:** Joey’s friend ten years later. Provides contrast and realism — he wasn’t there to see the “heroics.” Grounded, observant, a reminder that nostalgia and truth rarely match.

**🌇 OLDER JOEY (Late teens–20s)**
**Description:** Once full of imagination, now hardened by betrayal. Still searching for something heroic in a world that let him down. His closing narration brings the story full circle.

**📅 Production Notes**
* **Setting:** Urban neighborhood; mostly night exteriors.
* **Tone:** Visual realism with moments of childhood wonder.
* **Themes:** Hero worship, family, addiction, disillusionment, legacy.
* **Shooting Length:** 10–12 pages (~10–15 minutes).

CASTING CALL - Unpaid Independent Short Film.

TITLE: Ringer

**Production Type:** Independent Short Film

**Location:** Arvada, Northglenn, Colorado.

**Compensation:** Unpaid

**Union Status:** Non-Union

**Filming Window:** End of March

LOGLINE: A Manic pixie Dream Girl type plot goes south when the characters become aware that they're in a movie.

GENRE: Horror

ROLES:

CRAIG - (Male, 20s): A very down to earth and relatable guy, who has a special interest in music, but is also somewhat shy at times and will hesitate before speaking up for himself.

DECEMBER - (Female, 20s): A quirky manic pixie dream girl, who loves filmmaking, especially really old films from the 30s - 50s, and appears very happy and bubbly, but holds a darker side when she begins to questions the things around her.

SOPHIE - (Female, 20s): A punk rock tomboy who appears tough on the surface, but has a soft side underneath. While she has suffered through past trauma, she doesn’t stop it from letting her care about any of her friends.

NOTE: We are especially looking for actors who can do great improv and can play the character, and a fictionalized version of themselves. 

TO SUBMIT: Please email at alecopedia@gmail.com with a message saying you are interested and the subject line, “Ringer Audition - [INSERT ACTOR NAME]”. From there you will be given a link to a folder, where you may submit your Headshot, Resume, and Reel, along with an Audition Side of each character you want to audition for.

DEADLINE: Friday, January 16th

PILOT / PROMO / FESTIVAL-KORTFILM

VIKINGEPERIODEN

Kun 5 dages optagelse + en dags opsamling.

Passionsprojekt med stjernespækket cast og crew

Prisvindende instruktør og fotograf

Optagelser:

Brøndbyskoven / Albertslund Vikingelandsby

Det bliver Uge 9–10 (februar) måske før man må lige være lidt flex!

Vi søger:

10 årig pige skandinavisk udseende langt hår rødt / lysebrunt / mørkeblond 

 • 2 Runners med gyldigt kørekort til pack up pack down og ad hoc opgaver

 • Makeup & hår – fletninger i skæg og hår og war paint 

Forplejning:

Der er frokost på settet hver dag – og enkelte dage også aftensmad.

Medbring selv drikkevarer.

Vilkår:

Sorry not sorry – det er ikke nemt at lave film uden budget.

Til gengæld får du erfaring, netværk og et stærkt projekt på CV’et.

Det bliver skide skægt og mega spændende 🔥

Kontakt:

Send mail til yummiversal@gmail.com

Emnefelt: VIKING

Nürnberg! Wir laden euch zum Networking-Treffen am 12.01. ein! Offen für alle (semi)professionellen Schauspieler, Filmemacher oder Creative aus der Branche, die sich vernetzen möchten und 2026 gemeinsam Projekte umsetzen möchten :)
Unser Acting Circle war ursprünglich für Schauspieler gedacht, die gemeinsam proben, Schauspieltechniken erarbeiten oder sich über das Business austauschen wollten! 2026 möchte wir aktiver in das Filmen und Produzieren gehen, einige unserer Teilnehmer schreiben bereits an ersten Skripten! 

Die Idee ist auch, etwa 1x/Monat ein Treffen auf die Beine zu stellen, an dem wir üben - hier sind natürlich auch Filmemacher oder Regiebegeisterte eingeladen, die sich auf der anderen Seite der Kamera ausprobieren möchten! 

Das Treffen soll dazu dienen, sich unverbindlich kennenzulernen! Da unsere Räumlichkeiten nur begrenzt Platz bieten, ist eine Teilnahme nur mit vorheriger Anmeldung möglich! Schick uns über Instagram ein paar Infos zu dir und deinen bisherigen Erfahrungen zu!

Instagram.com/actingcircle 

Wir freuen uns auf deine Nachricht!

items.text:
Hey-Yah All ! Ein gesundes neues Jahr an alle.

Wir haben schon in einigen Filmen mitgespielt, auch in Serien.

Mein Mann hatte eine Rolle in "Unser Letzter Sommer" von Michal Rogalski. 

In Frankreich war er für den offiziellen D´Artagnan Verein der berühmte Musketier und hatte auch in der Fechtszene einen Namen.

Für die Szenen, Ausrüstung, zeitgnössische Fechtkleidung, Szenenbild, Training der Fechter, sowie das Fechten selbst im damaligen Stil zeichnete sich mein Mann im Film "Race" (Zeit für Legenden) aus: Roland Sonntag @ IMDB.

Wir schreiben und performen aktuell den guten alten Rock´n Roll auf unsere eigene neue Art und Weise.

Das Bild entstand auf der RBB Bühne Antenne Brandenburg der Berliner Woche letztes Jahr, woe wir das MKC -  Multikulturelles Centrum Templin e.V. offiziell vertraten. Die gesamte Meesehalle tanzte, sang und feierte.

Wir stehen gerne weiterhin für Film, TV, Werbung und besonders gerne auch für einen Genre-Film zur Verfügung. Uns gibt es immer nur im Doppelpack, weswegen wir z.B. schon 2 Anfragen für eine Kultserie abgesagt hatten. Man wollte nur Brigitte mit dem Kontrabass. Sorry. Wir sind unzertrennlich.

Natürlich lassen wir uns auch sehr gerne für Konzerte und Festivals buchen.

items.summary:
Hey-Yah All ! Ein gesundes neues Jahr an alle.

Wir haben schon in einigen Filmen mitgespielt, auch in Serien.

Mein Mann hatte eine Rolle in "Unser Letzter Sommer" von Michal Rogalski. 

In Frankreich war er für den offiziellen D´Artagnan Verein der berühmte Musketier und hatte auch in der Fechtszene einen Namen.

Für die Szenen, Ausrüstung, zeitgnössische Fechtkleidung, Szenenbild, Training der Fechter, sowie das Fechten selbst im damaligen Stil zeichnete sich mein Mann im Film "Race" (Zeit für Legenden) aus: Roland Sonntag @ IMDB.

Wir schreiben und performen aktuell den guten alten Rock´n Roll auf unsere eigene neue Art und Weise.

Das Bild entstand auf der RBB Bühne Antenne Brandenburg der Berliner Woche letztes Jahr, woe wir das MKC -  Multikulturelles Centrum Templin e.V. offiziell vertraten. Die gesamte Meesehalle tanzte, sang und feierte.

Wir stehen gerne weiterhin für Film, TV, Werbung und besonders gerne auch für einen Genre-Film zur Verfügung. Uns gibt es immer nur im Doppelpack, weswegen wir z.B. schon 2 Anfragen für eine Kultserie abgesagt hatten. Man wollte nur Brigitte mit dem Kontrabass. Sorry. Wir sind unzertrennlich.

Natürlich lassen wir uns auch sehr gerne für Konzerte und Festivals buchen.

Außer ein paar kleinen privaten Youtube Filmchen und unseren Facebook Account machten wir bisher keine Werbung. 

Viele liebe Grüße an alle, auch an die die wir nicht kennen, Euer Ronny Guittar Duo mit Brigitte Bass Vom Duo

**Er du mellem 12 og 24 år – og har du lyst til at være med i en kampagne, der gør en forskel?**🎬

Til en ny kampagne for **Genklang** søger vi børn og unge, både drenge og piger, der har lyst til at medvirke i en kampagnevideo, som skal deles på Genklangs sociale medier og online univers.

**Om kampagnen: *****Når ferien larmer mest***

Ferier forbindes ofte med frihed og glæde.
Men for mange børn og unge kan ferier være svære – fordi skolen og fritidsaktiviteter holder lukket, og man er mere hjemme, end man har lyst til.

Med kampagnen “Når ferien larmer mest” vil vi vise små, genkendelige øjeblikke, hvor unge forsøger at trække sig, gemme sig eller finde ro. Kampagnen skal skabe genkendelse og vise, at man ikke er alene.

**Hvem er Genklang?**

Genklang er et tilbud – både fysisk og online – for børn og unge mellem 12 og 24 år, som vokser op i hjem med alkohol- eller stofproblematikker. Genklang er finansieret af Social- og Boligstyrelsen og åbnede d. 1. september. Du kan læse mere her: [https://genklang.dk/](https://genklang.dk/) 

**👉 Vi søger dig, hvis du:**
* er mellem **12 og 24 år**
* har lyst til at medvirke i en **meningsfuld kampagne**

Du behøver **ikke** have skuespilerfaring.

Optagelserne foregår i Aarhus, og vi sørger selvfølgelig for at dække transport i forbindelse med medvirken.

**📩 Interesseret eller nysgerrig?**

Skriv til os på:
**caou@carelink.dk**

Har du spørgsmål, er du meget velkommen til at kontakte os – også bare for at høre mere.

items.text:
Hello everyone,

 

Join the one and only Mark Winstanley for a 4-week online course: Playing with Life's Gestures

 

Mark is an inspirational teacher who has taught at some of the most prestigious theatre and acting schools in the world, including the École Philippe Gaulier, the Royal Academy of Dramatic Art (RADA), and East 15 Acting School.

** **

*"A playful provocateur, he guides his students towards discovering their unique sense of pleasure, presence, and freedom in performance"*

 

Over the four weeks you will study the language of gesture and movement as a pathway to creative freedom.

 

Every Tuesday between the 3rd of February and the 24th of February on Zoom between 7pm and 9pm (UK time).

 

This workshop is open to anyone wanting to dig further into their acting practice.

 

Pay what you can, we suggest £80 for the whole course.

 

Email us to register your interest on theperformersplayground@gmail.com or book here: https://www.theperformersplayground.com/online-course

🎤 NATIONWIDE CASTING CALL – SINGERS WANTED 🎤
We are seeking strong vocalists and musical-theatre-style performers for well-paid solo and duo Care Home touring work launching throughout 2026.

Auditions will take place in February, and we’re inviting performers from all regions of the UK to apply.

Audition hubs:

 • SW London (for all London-based)

 • Bristol (South West)

 • Birmingham (Midlands)

 • Leeds (North East)

 • Manchester (North West)

With multiple new shows in a variety of styles launching across 2026, this is an exciting opportunity for reliable, engaging performers who love connecting with audiences.

📩 To apply:

Please email auditionsuk2025@gmail.com with:

 • A brief introduction about yourself

 • Your showreel or a rough vocals video

🚗 Driving licence essential

Heimatbewusstsein: Ist Patriotismus heute nötig, oder schon gefährlich? 

Du bekommst in 90 Sekunden eine klare Perspektive auf Zugehörigkeit, Identität und innere Heimat. 

Pfarrer Nils Petrat parkt sein gelbes Checker Taxi in Köln und stellt uns eine Frage, die in einer globalisierten, oft unübersichtlichen Welt plötzlich wieder überall auftaucht: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein heute, und wie stehst Du zu Patriotismus, Nationalstolz und diesem spürbaren Heimattrend? 

In dieser Folge sind Sandra und ich, Christian, als exklusive Interviewpartner dabei. Ich formuliere es bewusst so, wie es viele Menschen fühlen, aber selten sauber aussprechen: 

In einem gesunden Maß, ohne Gewalt, ohne Hass, ohne Überhöhung, kann Nationalstolz und Patriotismus etwas sein, das Halt gibt. Für mich gehört das Wissen, woher man kommt, zu den Grundbedürfnissen des Menschen. Es geht um Zugehörigkeit, und genau deshalb spielen Menschen, Gruppen, Orte, kulturelle Güter, religiöse Werke und Feste eine zentrale Rolle. Das kann etwas Kostbares sein, etwas, das man sichtbar pflegt, nicht als Kampfansage, sondern als Ausdruck von Wertschätzung. 

Spannend wird es dort, wo Heimat nicht nur als Ort verstanden wird, sondern als innerer Zustand. Als Christ hat Heimat für mich vor allem eine innere Dimension: ein seelisches Zuhause, ein innerer Hafen. Und genau hier entsteht der eigentliche Konflikt unserer Zeit, denn viele Debatten behandeln Heimat wie ein reines Außen, Flagge, Symbol, Folklore. Dabei geht es im Kern um Bindung, Sinn, Sicherheit, Gemeinschaft und Identität. 

Wenn man das übersieht, versteht man auch nicht, warum Menschen so emotional reagieren, wenn das Thema Heimat in Schlagzeilen, Talkshows oder Social Media auftaucht. 

Credits und Kontext, damit alles transparent bleibt: ProSieben, MOTZmobil. Video: © Alpha Entertainment / KHFA. Redaktion und Produktion: Patrik Kubik, Alpha Entertainment Film- und Fernsehproduktion GmbH, Oberländer Ufer 174, 50968 Köln Marienburg. 

Zuschauerfrage am Ende: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein für Dich ganz persönlich, und wo verläuft Deine Grenze zwischen gesundem Stolz und gefährlicher Ideologie? 

Gefällt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke und gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, damit mehr Menschen sachlich mitdiskutieren. 

Christian Weiße aka @christian_ugc_creator & Sandra Wötzel aka @sanny4me 

#Motzmobil #ProSieben #Heimatbewusstsein #Patriotismus #Nationalstolz #Heimat

“We’re Hiring!!  

CAPE TOWN ONLY PLEASE!

We are seeking a dynamic, charismatic, and articulate Game Show Host to lead our live and recorded show in Africa’s first ever live studio!  
The ideal candidate will bring energy, professionalism, and charm to every broadcast, engaging audiences while maintaining the integrity and excitement of the show.  

This is a front-facing role that requires confidence on camera, quick thinking, a sense of humour and an ability to connect naturally with diverse audiences.  

SO LADIES (aged 18-35 and also between 167cm & 175m tall) please get in touch for more details!  

How to Apply: Please submit your CV, headshot, and demo reel or showreel (if available) to  recruit@ppgafrica.com

Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.
